2.2.7 Exceptions to Requirement for Consent  
(Sections 18 to 52 of the CPPA) 
There are six categories of exceptions that allow for the collection, use or disclosure 
of personal information without the individual’s knowledge or consent: 
• the organization’s business activities (sections 18 to 28); 
• public interest (sections 29 to 39); 
• investigations (sections 40 to 42);

